query.comment:
Here, the model was trained with
strategy GoFastPart = minE(U) [<=4000] {Tanks.location} -> {T, F, D, chour}: <> time>=4000
in a setup with 'normal' demand structure and U' == 1 if tanks are either full or empty and U' == 0 otherwise. This produced a strategy that takes up 5600 lines in json format (saved as 'GoFastPart_4000_output.json'). This is the same as the strategy saved under the name 'GoFastNoUShort_output.json', which was trained in the same way. However, between these training sessions, I have trained using the same query but gotten different results - several strategies, that didn't work very well and also some that took up 7000-10000 lines in json.
